        <link:link rdf:resource="#item_1360"/>
        <dc:title>Bounded Formation Stability of Discrete-Time Multi-Agent Systems Under Data Rate Constraint</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>In this paper, we study the formation control problem for discrete-time multi-agent systems (MASs) under data rate constraint and bounded process noises. To be more speciﬁc, we aim to design a distributed control law for the MASs with a directed topology, such that the desired formation pattern can be achieved with a uniformly bounded error. To this end, a distributed strategy inspired by interaction rules in pigeon ﬂocks is proposed to construct the system topology. The generated topology is guaranteed to contain a directed spanning tree, and the nonzero eigenvalues of the corresponding Laplacian matrix can be directly adjusted with the weight of each connection. Based on the generated topology, we design a distributed formation control law considering the constrained data rate and bounded process noises. Rigorous stability analysis reveals that the formation error of the MASs maintains uniformly bounded with our topology construction and control law design. Finally, simulation results corroborate the effectiveness of the proposed methods and verify our theoretical analysis.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2024-7-28</dc:date>
        <z:language>en</z:language>
        <z:libraryCatalog>DOI.org (Crossref)</z:libraryCatalog>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
                <rdf:value>https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10661684/</rdf:value>
            </dcterms:URI>
        </dc:identifier>
        <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2025-11-11 08:16:58</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
        <dc:rights>https://doi.org/10.15223/policy-029</dc:rights>
        <bib:pages>5381-5387</bib:pages>
        <bib:presentedAt>
